<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1327,2036]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1436,1460]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" reason="1">Morphology.</emphasis>
Female (from IR21-2011) — Idiosoma L/W 731/622; L between anterior end of Cx-I and posterior end of Cx-IV 478, Cx-III W 464; apodemes of Cx-I long, extending posteriorly beyond the suture line between Cx-III and –IV. 
<figureCitation box="[332,433,1508,1532]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1239,1262]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,320,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-241@40.[151,1436,303,1218]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 28A–B. Neumania maharashtris Cook, 1967, female, IR21-2011: A = coxal and genital field; B = palp. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 28A</figureCitation>
shows the coxal area. Genital field W 242; acetabular plate L/W 85/63, 10-11 acetabula on each side; egg maximum diameter 111. Palp: total L 306, dL: P-1, 29; P-2, 94; P-3, 57; P-4, 94; P-5, 32; P-2/P-4 ratio, 1.0; P-4 with a short anteroventral tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[721,825,1580,1604]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="40.[151,250,1239,1262]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,320,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-241@40.[151,1436,303,1218]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 28A–B. Neumania maharashtris Cook, 1967, female, IR21-2011: A = coxal and genital field; B = palp. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
). Chelicera total L 121; dL of I-L-2-6: 125, 147, 184, 178, 161; dL of IV-L: 81, 106, 122, 169, 195, 193; first (
<figureCitation box="[814,919,1615,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1373,1396]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,193,1352]" captionTargetId="figure-330@41.[181,1405,173,1359]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 29A–B. Neumania maharashtris Cook, 1967, female, IR21-2011: A = I-L-2-6; B = IV-L. Scale bar = 100 µm." pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 29A</figureCitation>
) and second leg with long fluted or grooved setae. Swimming setae numbers: II-L-4 one, II-L-5 one, III-L-3 one, III-L-4 five, III-L-5 three, IV-L-3 one to two, IV-L-4 three and IV-L-5 three.
</paragraph>
